comment.en: A protective device breaks an electrical circuit when a stated electric current that passes through it is exceeded. A protective device provides protection against electrical current only (not as a general protective device). It may be used to represent the complete set of elements including both the tripping unit and the breaking unit that provide the protection. This may be particularly useful at earlier stages of design where the approach to breaking the electrical supply may be determined but the method of tripping may not. Alternatively, this entity may be used to specifically represent the breaking unit alone (in which case the tripping unit will also be specifically identified). This entity is specific to dedicated protective devices and excludes electrical outlets that may have circuit protection.
comment.es: Un dispositivo de proteccin interrumpe un circuito elctrico cuando se supera la corriente elctrica establecida que pasa a travs de l. Un dispositivo de proteccin slo proporciona proteccin contra la corriente elctrica (no como dispositivo de proteccin general). Puede utilizarse para representar el conjunto completo de elementos que incluyen tanto la unidad de disparo como la unidad de corte que proporcionan la proteccin. Esto puede resultar especialmente til en las primeras fases del diseo, en las que puede determinarse el mtodo de corte del suministro elctrico, pero no el mtodo de disparo. Alternativamente, esta entidad puede utilizarse para representar especficamente la unidad de corte sola (en cuyo caso la unidad de disparo tambin se identificar especficamente). Esta entidad es especfica de los dispositivos de proteccin dedicados y excluye las tomas de corriente que puedan tener proteccin de circuito.

comment.en: A control element that senses and regulates the humidity of a system or space so that the humidity is maintained near a desired setpoint.

comment.en: A type of vessel launch & recovery facility, also known as a hydraulic lift dock, where ships are lifted vertically by water impounding systems, then floated laterally across the land to berths which subsequently become dry.

comment.en: Designated level crossing over a road for pedestrians.

comment.en: An engine is a device that converts fuel into mechanical energy through combustion.

comment.en: Heating coil using electricity as a heating source.

comment.en: Type of building element that is usually used to transmit loads from superstructure to substructure, and usually allowing movement (displacement or rotation) in one or more degrees of freedom. It is typically a mechanical component procured as a whole and installed on site, but in simple cases it may be built on site (composed of other building elements, element components, etc.).
comment.es: Tipo de elemento constructivo que suele utilizarse para transmitir cargas de superestructura a subestructura, y que suele permitir movimientos (desplazamiento o rotacin) en uno o ms grados de libertad. Normalmente es un componente mecnico adquirido en su totalidad e instalado en obra, pero en casos simples puede construirse en obra (compuesto por otros elementos constructivos, componentes de elementos, etc.).

comment.en: Valve that closes off flow in a pipeline.

comment.en: A transport equipment is a network element responsible for providing functionality of transport, multiplexing, switching, management and supervision of transmission channels between different hosts. The data transport service uses three specific metrics: the bandwidth, the jitter, and the packet loss rate.

El servicio de transporte de datos utiliza tres mtricas especficas: el ancho de banda, el jitter y la tasa de prdida de paquetes.

comment.en: A natural navigable watercourse (such as a river) that needs to be managed or have improvements applied. This includes defined navigational areas in open seas and bays. NOTE definition in ISO 6707: open passage for conveying or containing water

comment.en: A cable arranger is a flexible accessory or a part of a component placed around cables to arrange and minimize flexing of them at the point where it is placed.
comment.es: Un organizador de cables es un accesorio flexible o una parte de un componente que se coloca alrededor de los cables para organizarlos y minimizar su flexin en el punto donde se coloca.

comment.en: Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a roller mounted on the eccentric of a shaft with a single vane in the nonrotating cylindrical housing.

comment.en: A fitting with typically two ports used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.

comment.en: Sealed systems that consist of an evaporator, a condenser, interconnecting piping, and an intermediate working fluid that is present in both liquid and vapor phases where the evaporator and the condenser are usually at opposite ends of a bundle of straight, individual thermosiphon tubes and the exhaust and supply ducts are adjacent to each other.

comment.en: A longitudinal facility part encompassing a linear portion of the facility defined by some uniform characteristics, or a transition between segments of uniform characteristics.
comment.es: Parte longitudinal de una infrastructura que abarca una porcin lineal de la infrastructura definida por algunas caractersticas uniformes, o una transicin entre segmentos de caractersticas uniformes.

comment.en: A fiber segment is an individual optical fiber used in telecommunication systems to transmit data by means of optical signals.
comment.es: Un segmento de fibra es una fibra ptica individual utilizada en sistemas de telecomunicaciones para transmitir datos mediante seales pticas.

comment.en: A small, local electrical appliance for cooling water. A freestanding water cooler is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
comment.es: Pequeo aparato elctrico local para enfriar agua. Un refrigerador de agua independiente es un aparato 'enchufado' cuya carga puede retirarse de un circuito elctrico

comment.en: A fastening connection where glue is used to join together elements.
comment.es: Conexin donde se utiliza cola para unir elementos.

comment.en: The covering is used to represent a molding being a strip of material to cover the transition of surfaces (often between wall cladding and ceiling).
comment.es: El cubrimiento se utiliza para representar una moldura que es una tira de material para cubrir la transicin de superficies (a menudo entre el revestimiento de la pared y el techo).

comment.en: A vibration damper is a device used to minimize the effects of vibration in a structure by dissipating kinetic energy. The damper may be passive (elastic, frictional, inertia) or active (in a system using sensors and actuators).
comment.es: Un amortiguador de vibraciones es un dispositivo que se utiliza para minimizar los efectos de las vibraciones en una estructura mediante la disipacin de energa cintica. El amortiguador puede ser pasivo (elstico, de friccin, de inercia) o activo (en un sistema que utiliza sensores y actuadores).

comment.en: Part of a road.
comment.es: Parte de una carretera.

comment.en: A structure on the carriageway to control the speed of vehicles.
comment.es: Estructura en la calzada para controlar la velocidad de los vehculos.

comment.en: Lateral road part separating two carriageways of the same road or separating traffic lanes and sidewalk.Definition from ISO 6707-1: area that separates the carriageways of a road with dual carriageways, (US:Median, UK:Central reservation).
comment.es: Parte lateral de la carretera que separa dos calzadas de la misma carretera o que separa los carriles de circulacin y la acera. Definicin de ISO 6707-1: zona que separa las calzadas de una carretera con doble calzada, (US:Median, UK:Central reservation).

comment.en: A solid state lamp that uses light-emitting diodes as the source of light whose emissive electroluminescent layer is composed of a film of organic compounds.

comment.en: A device that senses or detects heat.

comment.en: Water-cooled condenser with unspecified operation.

comment.es: La parte del puente que se extiende horizontalmente y transfiere la carga del trfico a las subestructuras del puente.

comment.en: At-grade junction where two or more roads meet or cross. Intersections may be further classified by number of road segments, traffic controls, and/or lane design.

comment.en: A device that will electrically open the circuit after a period of prolonged, abnormal current flow.
comment.es: Dispositivo que abre elctricamente el circuito tras un periodo prolongado de flujo anormal de corriente.

comment.en: A device that senses or detects the seismic wave and measures the seismic intensity in case of earthquake.
comment.es: Dispositivo que percibe o detecta la onda ssmica y mide la intensidad ssmica en caso de terremoto.

comment.en: An indirect connection made through the medium of the viscosity of a fluid.
comment.es: Conexin indirecta realizada a travs de la viscosidad de un fluido.

comment.en: A flow meter is a device that is used to measure the flow rate in a system.
comment.es: Un medidor de flujo es un dispositivo que se utiliza para medir la cantidad  de flujo en un sistema.

comment.en: Water cooled chiller.
comment.es: Enfirador Refrigerado por Agua

comment.en: A device that thermostatically actuates a control element.
comment.es: Dispositivo que acciona termostticamente un elemento de control.

comment.en: A transformer that converts from direct current (DC) to alternating current (AC).
comment.es: Un conversor que convierte de corriente continua (DC) a corriente alterna (AC).

comment.en: A longitudinal spatial part of a waterway or port facility that forms the gate, supporting structure & plant of an impounded facility such as a ship lock, dry dock or hydrolift.
comment.es: Parte espacial longitudinal de una va navegable o instalacin portuaria que forma la compuerta, la estructura de soporte y la planta de una instalacin inmovilizada, como una esclusa, un dique seco o un hidroelevador.

comment.en: An open or closed container used for storing a fluid at ambient pressure and from which it can be supplied to the fluid distribution system. There are many examples of storage tanks, such as potable water storage tanks, fuel storage tanks, etc.
comment.es: Recipiente abierto o cerrado que sirve para almacenar un fluido a presin ambiente y desde el que se puede suministrar al sistema de distribucin de fluidos. Hay muchos ejemplos de tanques de almacenamiento, como los tanques de almacenamiento de agua potable, los tanques de almacenamiento de combustible, etc.

comment.en: A structure built up of beams, columns, etc. with moment-resisting joints, such as gantry
comment.es: Una estructura formada por vigas, columnas, etc. con juntas resistentes a momento.

comment.en: A device that senses or detects temperature.
comment.es: Dispositivo que detecta la temperatura.

comment.en: The reinforcing bar is a main bar.
comment.es: La barra de refuerzo es una barra principal.

comment.en: Electrical generator with a fuel-driven engine, for example a diesel-driven emergency power supply.
comment.es: Generador elctrico con motor de combustible, por ejemplo un suministro de energa de emergencia disel.

comment.en: The tendon is a strand.
comment.es: El tendn es un filamento.

comment.en: An air terminal is a terminating or origination point for the transfer of air between distribution system(s) and one or more spaces. It can also be used for the transfer of air between adjacent spaces.

comment.en: A mooring device is an active or passive built element who's primary function is to participate in the mooring of a vessel, this could be in the form of a bollard used as an attachment point for lines or active equipment such as quick release hooks.
comment.es: Un dispositivo de amarre es un elemento construido activo o pasivo cuya funcin principal es participar en el amarre de una embarcacin, puede ser en forma de bolardo utilizado como punto de enganche para cabos o de equipo activo como ganchos de liberacin rpida.

comment.en: Gravity damper closes from the force of gravity. Commonly operated by gravitational weight.
comment.es: La compuerta de gravedad se cierra por la fuerza de la gravedad. Normalmente se acciona por el peso de la gravedad.

comment.en: A covering is an element which covers some part of another element and is fully dependent on that other element.
comment.es: Un cubrimiento es un elemento que cubre alguna parte de otro elemento y depende totalmente de ese otro elemento.

comment.en: The slab is used to represent a landing within a stair or ramp.
comment.es: La losa se utiliza para representar un rellano dentro de una escalera o rampa.

comment.es: Un segmento del tablero del puente. Los segmentos pueden estar separados por juntas de construccin o de expansin.

comment.en: One or more chambers arranged to prevent the ingress of oil to a drain or sewer that retains the oil for later removal.

comment.es: La losa se utiliza para representar un forjado contra el suelo (y, por tanto, formando parte de la cimentacin).

comment.en: The bearing functionality is provided by convex dome in a concave basin.

comment.en: Closed box.

comment.en: An electronic receiver that detects, demodulates, and amplifies transmitted signals.
comment.es: Un receptor electrnico que detecta, demodula y amplifica las seales transmitidas.

comment.en: Combination of at least two predefined types of unitary control element.
comment.es: Combinacin de al menos dos tipos predefinidos de elemento de control unitario.

comment.en: A bearing which carries vertical load by compression of an (elastomeric) disc confined in a (steel) cylinder and which accommodates rotations by deformations of the disc.
comment.es: Un cojinete que soporta carga vertical por compresin de un disco (elastomrico) confinado en un cilindro (de acero) y que soporta rotaciones por deformaciones del disco.

comment.en: A device that prevents wearing of the rails throughout the flange of wheel to reduce noise emissions. It is often located at inner side of the outer rail in a curve or near turnouts (depends on function wearing or noise reduction).

comment.en: Waste water appliance for washing the excretory organs while sitting astride the bowl.
comment.es: Aparato de aguas residuales para lavar los rganos excretores sentado a horcajadas.

comment.en: A fitting that changes the route of the cable carrier.
comment.es: Un accessorio que cambia el recorrido del portacables.

label.es: Tramo de Escalera con Tramos de Caracol

comment.en: A stair flight with a walking line including straight and curved sections.
comment.es: Un tramo de escalera con una lnea de paso que incluye tramos rectos y curvos.

comment.en: An impervious layer that could be used for e.g. roof covering (below tiling - that may be known as sarking etc.) or as a damp proof course membrane; also, waterproofing material on a bridge structure (typically on top of bridge slab).
comment.es: Capa impermeable que puede utilizarse, por ejemplo, para el cubrimiento de tejados (por debajo de las tejas, que pueden denominarse sarking, etc.) o como membrana impermeabilizante; tambin, material impermeabilizante en la estructura de un puente (normalmente sobre la losa del puente).

comment.en: An alarm activation mechanism in which a protective glass has to be broken to enable a button to be pressed.
comment.es: Un mecanismo de activacin de alarma en el que es necesario romper un cristal protector para poder pulsar un botn.

comment.en: Positive-displacement rotary compressor using a roller mounted on the eccentric of a shaft with multiple vanes in the nontotating cylindrical housing.
comment.es: Compresor rotativo de desplazamiento positivo que utiliza un rodillo montado en la excntrica de un eje con mltiples paletas en la carcasa cilndrica no basculante.

comment.en: A selector switch has multiple positions, and may change the source or level of power or other setting (according to the switched port type).
comment.es: Un conmutador selector tiene varias posiciones y puede cambiar la fuente o el nivel de potencia u otro ajuste (segn el tipo de puerto conmutado).

comment.en: A cohesion pile

comment.es: ISO 6707: Puente cuyos principales elementos estructurales son cables catenarios de los que se suspende el tablero.

comment.en: A beam that forms part of a slab construction and acts together with the slab which it carries. Such beams are often of T-shape (therefore the English name), but may have other shapes as well, e.g. an L-Shape or an Inverted-T-Shape.

comment.en: A control element at which alarms are annunciated.
comment.es: Un elemento de control en el que se anuncian las alarmas.

comment.en: Air flows through the impeller axially with guide vanes and reduced running blade tip clearance.
comment.es: El aire fluye a travs del impulsor axialmente con paletas gua y espacio reducido en la punta de la pala.

comment.en: A rigid segment is continuous linear segment of pipe that cannot be deformed.
comment.es: Un segmento rgido es un segmento lineal continuo de tubera que no puede deformarse.

comment.en: A vertical element suspending a structure (such as bridge deck) from a suspension cable or an arch.
comment.es: Elemento vertical que suspende una estructura (como el tablero de un puente) de un cable de suspensin o de un arco.

comment.en: Chamber, on the line of a drain or discharge pipe, that prevents grease passing into a drainage system.

comment.en: Spring or weight loaded valve that automatically discharges to a safe place fluid that has built up to excessive pressure in pipes or fittings.
comment.es: Vlvula cargada por un resorte o peso que descarga automticamente a un lugar seguro el fluido que se ha acumulado a una presin excesiva en tuberas o accesorios.

label.es: Intercambiador de Placas Fijas de Flujo Paralelo

comment.en: Heat exchanger with moving parts and alternate layers of plates, separated and sealed from the exhaust and supply air stream passages with primary air entering at secondary air inlet location and exiting at secondary air outlet location.

comment.en: An interceptor is a device designed and installed in order to separate and retain deleterious, hazardous or undesirable matter while permitting normal sewage or liquids to discharge into a collection system by gravity.
comment.es: Un interceptor es un dispositivo diseado e instalado para separar y retener materias nocivas, peligrosas o indeseables mientras permite que las aguas residuales o lquidos normales se descarguen en un sistema de recoleccin por gravedad.

comment.en: Device that provides purified medical air, composed of an air compressor and air treatment line.
comment.es: Dispositivo que proporciona aire medicinal purificado, compuesto por un compresor de aire y una lnea de tratamiento de aire.

comment.en: A transformer that changes the frequency between circuits.
comment.es: Un conversor que cambia la frecuencia entre circuitos.

comment.en: Furniture for storing books or other items.
comment.es: Muebles para guardar libros u otros artculos.

comment.en: A roof having a single slope.
comment.es: Un tejado con una sola pendiente.

comment.en: The covering is used to insulate an element for thermal or acoustic purposes.
comment.es: El cubrimiento sirve para aislar un elemento con fines trmicos o acsticos.

comment.en: A cable carrier fitting is a fitting that is placed at junction or transition in a cable carrier system.
comment.es: Un accesorio portacables es un accesorio que se coloca en una unin o transicin en un sistema portacables.

comment.en: A passive or active device formed of a damper and impact panel that is mounted on the quayside to protect against vessel impact.

comment.en: A piece of equipment consisting of a series of bars or steps between two upright elements used for climbing up or down something
comment.es: Equipo formado por una serie de barras o peldaos entre dos elementos verticales que sirve para subir o bajar algo

comment.en: A signal is an active device that conveys information or instructions to users, by means of an audio, visual signal or a combination of both. An instance of Signal represents a singular signalling device in a larger assembled unit or connected system, such as an individual frame within a railway signal, a single light unit in a traffic light system or an audio signal or light mounted on a navigational buoy. Signals can be physically aggregated together into an assembly which can include multiple signal instances (and also sign instances) and the associated supporting structural elements such as a simple pole or a rigid frame gantry (see Signal Assembly for examples). Signals can be logically (functionally) grouped together into a signalling system (a type of distribution system) to represent a connected group of signals for example a group of traffic lights controlling an road intersection.
